  "texts": [
    "• Diffusion modelsDiffusion models, as investigated in \"Improved Training of Wasserstein GANs,\" are useful in situations where steady and effective training is required.",
    "They are especially beneficial for large-scale picture production applications, improving training stability and convergence.In a nutshell, GANs excel in tasks that require realistic sample generation, VAEs excel in tasks that require structured latent representations, flow-based models are useful for explicit density estimation and invertible mappings, and diffusion models improve training stability in large-scale generative tasks.",
    "The specific applications demonstrate the models' adaptability across several areas in the field of generative modeling.",
    "Choosing GAN over other generative models and beyondGenerative Adversarial Networks (GANs) are preferable to other generative models due to their advantages under certain circumstances.",
    "GANs are particularly well-suited to applications that require the generation of extremely realistic and visually appealing samples."
  ],
